Whenever we enable our robot, my team has been getting the following error:

[CAN SPARK] IDs: 20, 21, 22, 23, 24, 25, 26, 27, WPILIB or External HAL Error:
CAN: Message not found Periodic Status 2

We’re unable to send any input to the robot beyond enable/disable and are unsure how to fix this. We’ve rewired our robot twice now and there are no breaks in the CAN. When we connect a SPARK MAX to the Rev Hardware Client, every SPARK shows up in the list and we’ve verified that all of them have the correct IDs. Another weird thing about the error code is that we don’t have a CAN ID higher than 17, but the error code mentions IDs 20–27. Any help would be greatly appreciated!
